properties.areaDesc: Central Laramie Range and Southwest Platte County
properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued February 11 at 1:10PM MST until February 12 at 6:00AM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
* WHAT...West winds 35 to 45 MPH with gusts up to 65 MPH.

* WHERE...Bordeaux along Interstate 25 between Chugwater and
Wheatland.

* WHEN...Until 6 AM MST Wednesday.

* IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation. Expect dangerous travel for
light, high profile vehicles including camping and tractor
trailers. There will be a high risk for blow overs of these
types of vehicles.
properties.instruction:
A High Wind Warning means a hazardous high wind event is expected
or occurring. Sustained wind speeds of at least 40 mph or gusts of
58 mph or more can lead to property damage.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 AM MST WEDNESDAY
